==English==

===Noun===
'''sultan''' {{m}} (''plural:'' ''sultans'') '''sultana''' {{f}} (''plural:'' ''sultanas'')

===Etymology=== 
*The word ''sultan'' itself is derived from [[Arabic]] '''{{Unicode|سلطان}}''' '''{{Unicode|sūltān}}''',meaning strength and autority.

*''sultan'' means an absolute ruler of a [[Muslim]] [[state]] ([[sultanate]]) such as [[Oman]]/[[Brunei]] or an empire such as the [[Ottoman Empire]].

*The ''sultan's'' [[wife]] or [[concubine]] is a ''sultana''

